        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 9:03PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 903 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Farmerville, or 18 miles southwest of Huttig, moving southeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Farmerville, Bayou D Arbonne Lake, Spencer, Linville, and Rocky
Branch.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
